It takes them two days.
Even by the sound of the hammer falling, they can tell if the claw is already properly shaken.
The tolerance in which they move is minimal.
The hem can fly from zero to 0.13 millimeters above the surface of the aircraft.
That's roughly twice the thickness of a human hair.
When inspecting, it's the turn of a trained touch.
When the controller swipes over a row of rites, he can tell if any of them are out of tolerance.
Then he picks up the exact pervert.
